# Configured Features (26.1–26.2)

## Removed / replaced (26.1)

- Feature types **`flower`**, **`flower_no_bonemeal`**, **`random_patch`** are gone. Build patches with placement modifiers: `count` + `random_offset` (and friends) on a simple block feature.
- Bone-meal plantables: use configured feature tag `#can_spawn_from_bone_meal` (not flower-only).
- Renames: `forest_rock` → **`block_blob`** (needs `can_place_on`); `ice_spike` → **`spike`** (needs `state`, `can_place_on`, `can_replace`).
- Huge mushrooms need `can_place_on`.
- Trees: `force_dirt` / `dirt_provider` → **`below_trunk_provider`** (rule-based; **required** in 26.2 — no default).
- `disk.state_provider` must be a full block state provider (often `rule_based_state_provider`).

## New / expanded (26.2)

| Type | Notes |
|------|--------|
| `weighted_random_selector` | Pick one weighted placed feature |
| `sequence` | Run placed features in order; stop chain if one fails to place |
| `template` | Place a weighted structure template (optional `rotations`) |
| `speleothem` | Was `pointed_dripstone`; needs `base_block`, `pointed_block`, `replaceable_blocks` |
| `speleothem_cluster` | Was `dripstone_cluster`; same new block fields + renamed chance fields |

Also: `large_dripstone` needs `replaceable_blocks`; `column_radius` max is **16** (was 19).

### Required new fields

- **`lake`**: `can_place_feature`, `can_replace_with_air_or_fluid`, `can_replace_with_barrier` (block predicates).
- **`root_system`**: `level_test_distance`, `max_level_deviation` (vanilla uses `0`).
- **`multiface_growth`**: `block` is mandatory (vanilla: `glow_lichen`).

### Flexible ID fields

`cannot_replace`, `invalid_blocks`, `root_replaceable`, `replaceable` accept a **tag, single ID, or list of IDs**.

### Block predicate

`matching_biomes` — `{ "biomes": "<id|list|#tag>" }` for worldgen placement checks.
